value.0: Scattered bones, and considerable bloodstains cover and surround this obviously-sacrificial altar.
Whatever gigantic beast this is from must be important to these Sahuagin, for them to keep it on a pedestal in their temple.
The wood's rich grain adds an unexpected vibrancy to this humble cabinet. Whoever crafted it clearly did so with great love.
A rickety-looking desk, the wood rotting away in the salty water. Likely scrounged from one of the many sunken ships scattered across the seafloor.
The chain disappears into some unseen recess above you where it presumably activates some hidden mechanism.
